html: Off. Like a king, leading all his subjects to battle. (Calmet) — Whistle. He alludes to the custom of leading forth bees by music, chap. vii. 18. (St. Cyprian) — Earth. The Chaldeans, (chap. xli. 9., and Jeremias vi. 22.) and not the Romans, as some would suppose. — Swiftly. Like an eagle, Daniel vii. 4., and Jeremias xlviii. 40.
